00:32:49.815 --> 00:32:53.046
- Why?
- I don't know. Never been in a fight. You?

506
00:32:53.135 --> 00:32:56.969
- No. But that's a good thing.
- You can't know yourself if you haven't!

507
00:32:57.055 --> 00:32:59.285
I don't wanna die without any scars.

508
00:32:59.375 --> 00:33:03.493
- Come on. Hit me. before I lose my nerve.
- Oh. God. This is crazy.

509
00:33:03.575 --> 00:33:05.770
So go crazy! Let it rip.

510
00:33:05.855 --> 00:33:08.415
- I don't know about this.
- I don't either.

511
00:33:08.495 --> 00:33:11.453
Who gives a shit? No-one's watching.
What do you care?

512
00:33:11.535 --> 00:33:13.890
This is crazy. You want me to hit you?!

513
00:33:13.975 --> 00:33:15.966
That's right.

514
00:33:16.055 --> 00:33:19.127
- Where? Like. in the face?
- Surprise me.

515
00:33:21.215 --> 00:33:23.206
This is so fucking stupid.

516
00:33:33.655 --> 00:33:35.725
Motherfucker!

517
00:33:35.815 --> 00:33:37.806
He hit me in the ear!

518
00:33:37.895 --> 00:33:40.967
- Well. Jesus. I'm sorry.
- Ow. Christ!

519
00:33:41.055 --> 00:33:43.046
- Why the ear. man?
- I fucked it up.

520
00:33:43.135 --> 00:33:44.773
No. that was perfect.

521
00:33:57.135 --> 00:33:59.171
No. it's all right.

522
00:33:59.975 --> 00:34:01.966
It really hurts.

523
00:34:02.415 --> 00:34:04.406
Right.

524
00:34:04.735 --> 00:34:06.851
Hit me again.

525
00:34:06.935 --> 00:34:08.971
No. you hit me. Come on!

526
00:34:25.215 --> 00:34:27.604
We should do this again sometime.

527
00:34:39.895 --> 00:34:42.011
- Where's your car?
- What car?

528
00:34:52.095 --> 00:34:54.370
I don't know how Tyler found that house

529
00:34:54.455 --> 00:34:56.605
but he said he'd been there for a year.

530
00:34:56.695 --> 00:34:59.448
It looked like it was waiting to be torn down.

531
00:34:59.535 --> 00:35:01.844
Most of the windows were boarded up.

532
00:35:01.935 --> 00:35:07.055
There was no lock on the front door from
when the police. or whoever. kicked it in.

533
00:35:07.135 --> 00:35:09.126
The stairs were ready to collapse.

534
00:35:09.215 --> 00:35:11.649
I didn'tknow if he owned it or was squatting.

535
00:35:11.735 --> 00:35:14.124
Neither would have surprised me.

536
00:35:14.975 --> 00:35:16.966
Yep. That's you.

537
00:35:17.055 --> 00:35:19.523
That's me. That's the toilet. Good?

538
00:35:19.615 --> 00:35:21.606
Yeah. thanks.

539
00:35:21.695 --> 00:35:23.526
What a shithole.

540
00:35:23.615 --> 00:35:25.492
Nothing worked.

541
00:35:28.975 --> 00:35:32.763
Turning on one light meant
another light in the house went out.

542
00:35:32.855 --> 00:35:36.450
There were no neighbours.
Just warehouses and a papermill.

543
00:35:36.535 --> 00:35:40.369
That fart smell of steam.
The hamster-cage smell of wood chips.

544
00:35:42.055 --> 00:35:44.330
What have we here?

545
00:35:58.535 --> 00:36:00.571
- Hey. guys.
- Hey.

546
00:36:11.095 --> 00:36:14.053
Every time it rained. we had to kill the power.

547
00:36:14.895 --> 00:36:18.126
By the end of the first month.
I didn't miss TV.

548
00:36:19.135 --> 00:36:22.332
I didn't even mind the warm. stale refrigerator.

549
00:36:34.215 --> 00:36:36.206
Can I be next?

550
00:36:40.455 --> 00:36:42.446
All right. man.

551
00:36:42.535 --> 00:36:44.446
Lose the tie.

552
00:36:48.295 --> 00:36:52.493
At night. Tylerand I were alone
for half a mile in every direction.

553
00:36:57.735 --> 00:37:01.489
Rain trickled down through
the plaster and the light fixtures.

554
00:37:01.575 --> 00:37:04.294
Everything wooden swelled and shrank.

555
00:37:04.375 --> 00:37:07.447
Everywhere were rusted nails
to snagy our elbow on.

556
00:37:07.535 --> 00:37:10.003
The previous occupant had been a shut-in.

557
00:37:10.095 --> 00:37:12.086
Hey. man. What are you reading?

558
00:37:12.175 --> 00:37:16.373
Listen to this. It's an article written
by an organ in the first person.

559
00:37:16.455 --> 00:37:19.094
"I am Jack's medulla oblongata.
Without me.

560
00:37:19.175 --> 00:37:22.485
Jack could not regulate
his heart rate or breathing."

561
00:37:22.575 --> 00:37:24.566
There's a whole series of these.

562
00:37:24.655 --> 00:37:26.646
"I Am Jill's Nipples."

563
00:37:28.575 --> 00:37:32.409
- "I Am Jack's Colon."
- "I Get Cancer. I Kill Jack."

564
00:37:35.535 --> 00:37:39.164
After fighting. everything else
in life got the volume turned down.

565
00:37:39.255 --> 00:37:42.725
What?

566
00:37:42.815 --> 00:37:46.205
- You could deal with anything.
- Have you finished those reports?

567
00:37:50.695 --> 00:37:53.163
If you could choose.
who would you fight?

568
00:37:53.255 --> 00:37:55.246
I'd fight my boss. probably.

569
00:37:55.335 --> 00:37:57.371
Really?

570
00:37:57.455 --> 00:38:00.652
- Yeah. why? Who would you fight?
- I'd fight my dad.

571
00:38:00.735 --> 00:38:02.726
I don't know my dad.

572
00:38:02.815 --> 00:38:04.646
I mean. I know him. but...

573
00:38:04.735 --> 00:38:07.010
He left when I was like. six years old.

574
00:38:07.095 --> 00:38:09.973
Married this other woman
and had some other kids.

575
00:38:10.055 --> 00:38:12.046
He did this every six years.

576
00:38:12.135 --> 00:38:16.094
- He changes city and starts a new family.
- Fucker's setting up franchises!

577
00:38:16.895 --> 00:38:18.886
My dad never went to college.

578
00:38:18.975 --> 00:38:22.729
- So it was real important that I go.
- That sounds familiar.

579
00:38:22.815 --> 00:38:27.093
So I graduate. Call him up long-distance
and say. "Dad. now what?"

580
00:38:27.175 --> 00:38:29.086
- He says. "Get a job."
- Same here.

581
00:38:29.175 --> 00:38:31.735
Now I'm 25. Make my yearly call again.

582
00:38:31.815 --> 00:38:33.726
"Dad. now what?"

583
00:38:33.815 --> 00:38:35.851
He says. "I dunno. Get married."

584
00:38:35.935 --> 00:38:39.245
You can't get married.

585
00:38:39.975 --> 00:38:41.966
I'm a 30-year-old boy.

586
00:38:42.055 --> 00:38:44.444
We're a generation of men raised by women.

587
00:38:44.535 --> 00:38:48.608
I'm wondering if another woman
is really the answer we need.

588
00:38:54.375 --> 00:38:57.447
Most of the week. we were Ozzie and Harriet.

589
00:38:58.295 --> 00:39:01.605
But every Saturday night.
we were finding something out.

590
00:39:02.775 --> 00:39:06.085
We were finding out more and more
that we were not alone.

591
00:39:09.855 --> 00:39:14.326
It used to be that when I came home angry
or depressed. I'd just clean my condo.

592
00:39:14.415 --> 00:39:16.406
Polish my Scandinavian furniture.

593
00:39:16.495 --> 00:39:21.330
I should have been looking for a new condo
or haggling with my insurance company.

594
00:39:21.415 --> 00:39:25.044
I should have been upset
about my nice flaming little shit.

595
00:39:25.135 --> 00:39:26.966
But I wasn't.

596
00:39:27.055 --> 00:39:30.570
The premise of cybernetting an office
is make things more efficient.

597
00:39:30.655 --> 00:39:33.374
Monday mornings.
I just thought about next week.

598
00:39:33.455 --> 00:39:36.367
Can I get the icon in cornflower blue?

599
00:39:36.455 --> 00:39:37.524
Absolutely.

600
00:39:37.615 --> 00:39:40.732
Efficiency is priority No.1. people.

601
00:39:40.855 --> 00:39:43.528
Because waste is a thief.

602
00:39:43.615 --> 00:39:46.607
I showed this to my man here.
You liked it. didn't you?

603
00:39:50.135 --> 00:39:53.889
You can swallow a pint of blood
before you get sick.

604
00:39:54.895 --> 00:39:57.045
It was right in everyone's face.

605
00:39:57.135 --> 00:39:59.205
Tyler and I just made it visible.

606
00:39:59.295 --> 00:40:01.604
It was on the tip of everyone's tongue.

607
00:40:01.695 --> 00:40:03.686
Tyler and I just gave it a name.

608
00:40:14.455 --> 00:40:16.446
Come on. you've gotta go home!

609
00:40:37.775 --> 00:40:39.970
Turn off the jukebox. Lock the back.

610
00:41:00.055 --> 00:41:03.604
Every week.
Tyler gave the rules tha the and I decided.

611
00:41:03.695 --> 00:41:05.686
Gentlemen!

612
00:41:06.415 --> 00:41:08.406
Welcome to Fight Club.

613
00:41:10.455 --> 00:41:12.525
The first rule of Fight Club is

614
00:41:12.615 --> 00:41:14.890
you do not talk about Fight Club.

615
00:41:14.975 --> 00:41:17.443
The second rule of Fight Club is

616
00:41:17.855 --> 00:41:21.165
you do not talk about Fight Club!

617
00:41:21.255 --> 00:41:23.450
Third rule of Fight Club.

618
00:41:23.535 --> 00:41:26.208
Someone yells stop. goes limp. taps out.

619
00:41:26.295 --> 00:41:28.934
the fight is over. Fourth rule.

620
00:41:29.015 --> 00:41:31.245
Only two guys to a fight.

621
00:41:31.335 --> 00:41:33.132
Fifth rule.

622
00:41:33.215 --> 00:41:35.775
One fight at a time. fellas.

623
00:41:35.855 --> 00:41:38.244
Sixth rule. No shirts. No shoes.

624
00:41:38.335 --> 00:41:42.089
Seventh rule.
Fights will go on as long as they have to.

625
00:41:43.855 --> 00:41:46.323
And the eighth and final rule.

626
00:41:47.415 --> 00:41:50.487
If this is your first night at Fight Club

627
00:41:50.575 --> 00:41:52.566
you have to fight.

628
00:41:56.455 --> 00:41:58.446
This kid from work. Ricky.

629
00:41:58.535 --> 00:42:02.847
couldn't remember whether
you ordered pens with blue ink or black.

630
00:42:02.935 --> 00:42:05.244
But Ricky was a god for ten minutes

631
00:42:05.335 --> 00:42:08.532
when he trounced
the maitre d' of a local food court.

632
00:42:10.335 --> 00:42:15.455
Sometimes. all you could hear were
the flat. hard. packing sounds over the yelling.

633
00:42:19.055 --> 00:42:21.967
Or the wet choke
when someone gasped and sprayed...

634
00:42:22.055 --> 00:42:24.011
Stop!

635
00:42:24.095 --> 00:42:26.848
You weren't alive anywhere
like you were there.

636
00:42:26.935 --> 00:42:31.531
But Fight Club only exists in the hours
between when Fight Club starts and ends.

637
00:42:32.055 --> 00:42:34.967
Even if I could tell someone
they had a good fight.

638
00:42:35.055 --> 00:42:37.250
I wouldn't be talking to the same man.

639
00:42:37.335 --> 00:42:40.532
Who you were in Fight Club
is not who you were outside of it.

640
00:42:40.615 --> 00:42:45.450
A guy came to Fight Club for the first time.
His ass was a wad of cookie dough.

641
00:42:45.535 --> 00:42:48.254
After a few weeks. he was carved out of wood.

642
00:42:49.055 --> 00:42:52.127
If you could fight any celebrity.
who would you fight?

643
00:42:52.215 --> 00:42:55.207
- Alive or dead?
- Doesn't matter. Who'd be tough?

644
00:42:56.095 --> 00:42:59.087
Hemingway. You?

645
00:42:59.695 --> 00:43:02.732
Shatner. I'd fight William Shatner.

646
00:43:03.735 --> 00:43:06.807
We all started seeing things differently.

647
00:43:08.015 --> 00:43:11.246
Everywhere we went.
we were sizing things up.

648
00:43:14.455 --> 00:43:17.447
I felt sorry for guys packed into gyms.

649
00:43:17.535 --> 00:43:21.448
trying to look like how Calvin Klein
or Tommy Hilfiger said they should.

650
00:43:21.535 --> 00:43:23.571
Is that what a man looks like?

651
00:43:24.455 --> 00:43:27.174
Oh. self-improvement is masturbation.

652
00:43:27.255 --> 00:43:29.246
Now. self-destruction...

653
00:43:29.335 --> 00:43:31.246
Excuse me.

654
00:44:04.455 --> 00:44:07.527
Fight Club wasn'tabout winning or losing.

655
00:44:07.615 --> 00:44:09.606
It wasn't about words.

656
00:44:11.455 --> 00:44:14.811
The hysterical shouting was in tongues

657
00:44:14.895 --> 00:44:16.772
like at a Pentecostal Church.

658
00:44:21.135 --> 00:44:23.126
- Is that it?
- Stop!

659
00:44:23.215 --> 00:44:25.968
When the fight was over. nothing was solved.

660
00:44:26.055 --> 00:44:27.886
But nothing mattered.

661
00:44:27.975 --> 00:44:30.648
Cool.

662
00:44:30.735 --> 00:44:33.408
Afterwards. we all felt saved.

663
00:44:34.295 --> 00:44:36.490
Hey. man. How about next week?

664
00:44:36.575 --> 00:44:38.566
How about next month?!

665
00:44:38.655 --> 00:44:40.646
Everybody here in the middle.

666
00:44:40.735 --> 00:44:42.691
New guy. you too.

667
00:44:44.375 --> 00:44:46.445
Sometimes. Tyler spoke for me.

668
00:44:46.535 --> 00:44:48.526
He fell down some stairs.

669
00:44:49.175 --> 00:44:51.166
I fell down some stairs.

670
00:44:52.935 --> 00:44:57.406
Fight Club became the reason to cut
your hair short or trim your fingernails.

671
00:44:57.495 --> 00:44:59.884
OK. Any historical figure.

672
00:44:59.975 --> 00:45:01.772
I'd fight Gandhi.

673
00:45:02.375 --> 00:45:04.127
Good answer.

674
00:45:04.215 --> 00:45:06.365
- How about you?
- Lincoln.

675
00:45:06.455 --> 00:45:08.923
Lincoln?

676
00:45:09.015 --> 00:45:12.485
Big guy. big reach.
Skinny guys fight till they're burger.

677
00:45:13.335 --> 00:45:15.326
Fuck!

678
00:45:16.455 --> 00:45:19.049
Hey. even the Mona Lisa's falling apart.

679
00:45:27.775 --> 00:45:29.094
Hello?

680
00:45:29.175 --> 00:45:31.484
Where have you been the last eight weeks?

681
00:45:31.575 --> 00:45:32.803
Marla?

682
00:45:35.655 --> 00:45:38.692
- How did you find me?
- You left a forwarding number.

683
00:45:38.775 --> 00:45:41.653
I haven't seen you at any support groups.

684
00:45:41.735 --> 00:45:44.807
We split 'em up.
That was the idea. Remember?

685
00:45:44.895 --> 00:45:47.614
Yeah. but you haven't been going to yours.

686
00:45:47.695 --> 00:45:51.051
- How do you know?
- I cheated.

687
00:45:51.135 --> 00:45:52.887
I found a new one.

688
00:45:53.415 --> 00:45:55.610
- Really?
- It's for men only.

689
00:45:55.695 --> 00:45:57.208
Like the testicle thing?

690
00:46:00.815 --> 00:46:02.771
Look. this is a bad time.

691
00:46:02.855 --> 00:46:05.210
I've been going to Debtors Anonymous.

692
00:46:05.295 --> 00:46:08.685
- They're really fucked-up people...
- I'm on my way out.

693
00:46:08.775 --> 00:46:11.050
Me too. I've got a stomach full of Xanax.

694
00:46:11.135 --> 00:46:13.330
I took what was left of a bottle.

695
00:46:13.415 --> 00:46:15.406
It might have been too much.

696
00:46:15.495 --> 00:46:18.965
Picture Marla Singer throw herself
around her crummy apartment.

697
00:46:19.095 --> 00:46:23.407
This isn't a for-real suicide thing.
This is probably a cry-for-help thing.

698
00:46:23.495 --> 00:46:26.293
So you're staying in tonight. then?

699
00:46:26.375 --> 00:46:29.094
Do you wanna wait
and hear me describe death?

700
00:46:29.175 --> 00:46:33.487
Do you wanna listen
and see if my spirit can use a phone?

701
00:46:35.655 --> 00:46:38.215
Have you ever heard a death rattle before?

702
00:47:03.415 --> 00:47:08.045
Tyler's door was closed. I'd been here for
two months and his door was never closed.

703
00:47:12.855 --> 00:47:15.813
You won't believe this dream
I had last night.

704
00:47:15.895 --> 00:47:19.046
I can hardly believe anything about last night.

705
00:47:28.455 --> 00:47:30.332
What are you doing here?

706
00:47:32.935 --> 00:47:34.926
What?

707
00:47:35.015 --> 00:47:37.370
This is my house.
What are you doing here?

708
00:47:39.655 --> 00:47:41.566
Fuck you!

709
00:47:55.615 --> 00:47:58.812
Oh. you've got some fucked-up friends!

710
00:47:58.895 --> 00:48:00.806
Limber. though.

711
00:48:00.895 --> 00:48:02.806
Silly cooze.

712
00:48:03.855 --> 00:48:06.449
I come in last night. Phone's off the hook.

713
00:48:06.535 --> 00:48:08.526
Guess who's on the other end?

714
00:48:08.615 --> 00:48:10.731
I knew the story before he told me.

715
00:48:12.935 --> 00:48:16.371
Have you ever heard a death rattle before?

716
00:48:16.455 --> 00:48:19.174
Do you think it'll live up to its name?

717
00:48:19.255 --> 00:48:22.691
Or will it just be a death hairball?

718
00:48:25.975 --> 00:48:29.809
Prepare to evacuate soul.

719
00:48:29.895 --> 00:48:31.453
Ten.

720
00:48:31.535 --> 00:48:34.208
nine.... eight...

721
00:48:34.295 --> 00:48:36.445
How could Tyler. of all people.

722
00:48:36.535 --> 00:48:40.244
think it was a bad thing
that Marla Singer was about to die?

723
00:48:40.335 --> 00:48:41.893
Five.

724
00:48:41.975 --> 00:48:43.533
four...

725
00:48:44.255 --> 00:48:46.246
Hang on.

726
00:48:51.455 --> 00:48:53.685
You got here fast.

727
00:48:55.175 --> 00:48:57.166
Did I call you?

728
00:49:07.455 --> 00:49:10.447
The mattress is all sealed in slippery plastic.

729
00:49:13.535 --> 00:49:15.844
Oh. don't worry. It's not a threat to you.

730
00:49:18.535 --> 00:49:20.332
Oh. fuck!

731
00:49:20.415 --> 00:49:22.406
Somebody called the cops.

732
00:49:33.855 --> 00:49:37.211
- Hey. where's 513?
- End of the hall.

733
00:49:37.975 --> 00:49:41.684
The girl who lives there
used to be a charming. lovely girl.

734
00:49:41.775 --> 00:49:43.845
She has lost faith in herself.

735
00:49:43.935 --> 00:49:46.654
- Miss Singer. let us help you!
- She's a monster!

736
00:49:46.735 --> 00:49:50.694
- You have every reason to live.
- She's infectious human waste!

737
00:49:50.775 --> 00:49:54.404
- Miss Singer!
- Good luck trying to save her!

738
00:49:59.015 --> 00:50:01.131
If I fall asleep.

739
00:50:01.215 --> 00:50:03.365
I'm done for.

740
00:50:05.255 --> 00:50:07.371
You're gonna have to keep me up

741
00:50:07.455 --> 00:50:09.446
all night.

742
00:50:09.535 --> 00:50:11.765
Un-fucking-believable.

743
00:50:11.855 --> 00:50:13.925
He was obviously able to handle it.

744
00:50:14.015 --> 00:50:17.564
- You know what I mean. you fucked her.
- No. I didn't.

745
00:50:17.655 --> 00:50:19.646
- Never?
- No.

746
00:50:20.575 --> 00:50:22.566
You're not into her. are you?

747
00:50:22.655 --> 00:50:24.646
No! God. not at all.

748
00:50:24.735 --> 00:50:27.249
I am Jack's raging bile duct.

749
00:50:27.335 --> 00:50:29.212
Are you sure? You can tell me.

750
00:50:29.295 --> 00:50:31.092
Believe me. I'm sure.

751
00:50:31.175 --> 00:50:34.326
- Puta gun to my head and spray my brains.
- That's good.

752
00:50:34.415 --> 00:50:37.054
She's a predator posing as a house pet.
Stay away.

753
00:50:38.935 --> 00:50:42.450
The shit that came out of
this woman's mouth. I had never heard!

754
00:50:42.535 --> 00:50:44.127
