01:05:59.126 --> 01:06:01.356
Yeah. hey. to both of us. right?

996
01:06:01.446 --> 01:06:04.006
Have you heard about the guy
that invented it?

997
01:06:04.086 --> 01:06:06.884
- Yeah. actually...
- I hear all kinds of things.

998
01:06:06.966 --> 01:06:10.436
Supposedly.
he was born in a mental institution

999
01:06:10.526 --> 01:06:13.757
and he sleeps only one hour a night.

1000
01:06:13.846 --> 01:06:15.962
He's a great man.

1001
01:06:17.406 --> 01:06:19.601
Do you know about Tyler Durden?

1002
01:06:43.566 --> 01:06:45.557
I didn't hurt you. did I?

1003
01:06:45.646 --> 01:06:47.637
Actually. you did.

1004
01:06:47.726 --> 01:06:49.717
Thank you for this.

1005
01:06:49.966 --> 01:06:52.241
Thank you. thank you. thank you.

1006
01:06:52.326 --> 01:06:54.317
Fight Club.

1007
01:06:54.406 --> 01:06:56.442
This was mine and Tyler's gift.

1008
01:06:56.526 --> 01:06:56.566
Our gift to the world.

1009
01:06:56.566 --> 01:06:58.522
Our gift to the world.

1010
01:06:58.606 --> 01:07:01.803
I look around. I look around.
I see a lot of new faces.

1011
01:07:03.366 --> 01:07:05.482
Shut up!

1012
01:07:05.566 --> 01:07:10.242
Which means a lot of people have been
breaking the first two rules of Fight Club.

1013
01:07:18.206 --> 01:07:22.119
I see in Fight Club the strongest
and smartest men who've ever lived.

1014
01:07:22.206 --> 01:07:24.197
I see all this potential.

1015
01:07:24.286 --> 01:07:26.277
And I see it squandered.

1016
01:07:27.246 --> 01:07:30.238
Goddamn it.
an entire generation pumping gas.

1017
01:07:30.766 --> 01:07:32.757
Waiting tables.

1018
01:07:32.846 --> 01:07:34.837
Slaves with white collars.

1019
01:07:37.206 --> 01:07:40.164
Advertising has us chasing cars and clothes.

1020
01:07:40.246 --> 01:07:43.397
Working jobs we hate
so we can buy shit we don't need.

1021
01:07:47.126 --> 01:07:49.481
We're the middle children of history.

1022
01:07:49.566 --> 01:07:51.557
No purpose or place.

1023
01:07:51.726 --> 01:07:53.717
We have no Great War.

1024
01:07:54.046 --> 01:07:56.037
No Great Depression.

1025
01:07:57.726 --> 01:08:00.001
Our great war is a spiritual war.

1026
01:08:00.406 --> 01:08:03.637
Our great depression is our lives.

1027
01:08:06.366 --> 01:08:09.324
We've all been raised
on television to believe

1028
01:08:09.406 --> 01:08:12.921
that one day we'd be millionaires
and movie gods and rock stars.

1029
01:08:13.006 --> 01:08:14.997
But we won't.

1030
01:08:15.086 --> 01:08:17.441
We're slowly learning that fact.

1031
01:08:17.526 --> 01:08:19.881
And we're very. very pissed off.

1032
01:08:19.966 --> 01:08:21.524
Yeah!

1033
01:08:24.326 --> 01:08:28.604
- First rule of Fight Club is. do not talk...

1034
01:08:33.846 --> 01:08:35.074
Who are you?

1035
01:08:35.886 --> 01:08:38.400
- Who am I?
- Yeah.

1036
01:08:39.246 --> 01:08:41.965
There's a sign on the front
that says Lou's Tavern.

1037
01:08:43.006 --> 01:08:46.715
I'm fucking Lou. Who the fuck are you?

1038
01:08:46.806 --> 01:08:48.797
Tyler Durden.

1039
01:08:51.806 --> 01:08:55.116
Who told you motherfuckers
that you could use my place?

1040
01:08:55.206 --> 01:08:57.481
We have a deal worked out with Irvine.

1041
01:08:57.566 --> 01:09:00.034
Irvine's at home with a broken collarbone.

1042
01:09:00.126 --> 01:09:02.196
He don't own this place. I do.

1043
01:09:04.286 --> 01:09:07.596
- How much money's he getting for this?
- There is no money.

1044
01:09:07.686 --> 01:09:10.359
- Free to all.
- Ain't that something?

1045
01:09:10.446 --> 01:09:12.198
It is. actually.

1046
01:09:12.286 --> 01:09:14.641
Look. stupid fuck!

1047
01:09:14.726 --> 01:09:17.160
- I want everybody out of here right now.
- Hey!

1048
01:09:17.246 --> 01:09:19.396
You should join our club.

1049
01:09:19.766 --> 01:09:21.677
Did you hear what I just said?

1050
01:09:21.766 --> 01:09:23.757
You and your friend.

1051
01:09:25.606 --> 01:09:27.597
You hear me now?

1052
01:09:29.726 --> 01:09:31.717
No. I didn't quite catch that. Lou.

1053
01:09:37.606 --> 01:09:39.517
Still not getting it.

1054
01:09:40.526 --> 01:09:42.596
OK. OK. I got it.

1055
01:09:42.686 --> 01:09:45.041
I got it. I got it. Shit. I lost it.

1056
01:09:46.046 --> 01:09:47.843
Back! All of you!

1057
01:09:49.486 --> 01:09:51.477
Everybody back!

1058
01:09:58.646 --> 01:10:00.716
Ah. Lou!

1059
01:10:00.806 --> 01:10:04.321
Come on. man!
We really like this place.

1060
01:10:13.006 --> 01:10:15.804
- That's right. Lou. Get it out.
- Shut the fuck up.

1061
01:10:15.926 --> 01:10:17.644
Oh. yeah!

1062
01:10:22.406 --> 01:10:24.397
Is that fucking funny?

1063
01:10:33.606 --> 01:10:36.074
Fucking guy is a loony. I'm telling you.

1064
01:10:36.886 --> 01:10:38.524
Unbelievable.

1065
01:10:42.566 --> 01:10:45.399
- You don't know where I've been. Lou.
- Oh. my God!

1066
01:10:45.486 --> 01:10:48.239
You don't know where I've been!

1067
01:10:51.206 --> 01:10:54.164
Please let us keep it. Lou! Please. Lou!

1068
01:10:54.246 --> 01:10:56.601
Fucking use the basement! Christ!

1069
01:10:56.686 --> 01:10:59.439
I want your word. Lou! I want your word!

1070
01:10:59.526 --> 01:11:01.437
On my mother's eyes.

1071
01:11:10.206 --> 01:11:12.197
Thanks. Lou.

1072
01:11:13.486 --> 01:11:15.477
You too. big guy.

1073
01:11:19.286 --> 01:11:21.277
We'll see you next week.

1074
01:11:36.166 --> 01:11:39.602
This week. each one of you
has a homework assignment.

1075
01:11:39.686 --> 01:11:44.316
You're gonna go out. You're gonna
start a fight with a total stranger.

1076
01:11:47.446 --> 01:11:49.516
You're gonna start a fight

1077
01:11:49.606 --> 01:11:51.597
and you're gonna lose.

1078
01:11:53.366 --> 01:11:53.406
Excellent choice. sir.

1079
01:11:53.406 --> 01:11:55.362
Excellent choice. sir.

1080
01:11:57.846 --> 01:12:00.997
Hey! Watch out. jackass! Come on!

1081
01:12:01.366 --> 01:12:03.926
Now. this is not as easy as it sounds.

1082
01:12:06.526 --> 01:12:08.403
Son of a bitch!

1083
01:12:08.486 --> 01:12:13.037
Most people. normal people.
do just about anything to avoid a fight.

1084
01:12:13.926 --> 01:12:15.917
Excuse me!

1085
01:12:16.006 --> 01:12:19.555
You sprayed me with your hose.
That's not necessary...

1086
01:12:19.646 --> 01:12:21.477
Jay! Go call 911!

1087
01:12:24.126 --> 01:12:26.082
Put the hose down.

1088
01:12:26.166 --> 01:12:28.157
Stop it! Stop it!

1089
01:12:29.766 --> 01:12:31.563
Sorry.

1090
01:12:46.446 --> 01:12:48.801
We need to talk.

1091
01:12:50.966 --> 01:12:52.957
OK.

1092
01:12:53.046 --> 01:12:55.037
Where to begin?

1093
01:12:55.126 --> 01:12:57.242
With your constant absenteeism?

1094
01:12:57.326 --> 01:12:59.760
With your unpresentable appearance?

1095
01:12:59.846 --> 01:13:01.802
You're up for review.

1096
01:13:01.886 --> 01:13:04.958
I am Jack's complete lack of surprise.

1097
01:13:05.046 --> 01:13:06.877
- What?
- Let's pretend.

1098
01:13:06.966 --> 01:13:09.719
You're the Department of Transportation.
OK?

1099
01:13:09.806 --> 01:13:13.321
Someone informs you that this company

1100
01:13:13.406 --> 01:13:17.319
installs front-seat mounting brackets
that failed collision tests.

1101
01:13:17.406 --> 01:13:20.682
brake linings that fail after 1.000 miles.

1102
01:13:20.766 --> 01:13:24.998
and fuel injectors
that explode and burn people alive.

1103
01:13:25.086 --> 01:13:26.883
What then?

1104
01:13:26.966 --> 01:13:29.161
Are you threatening me?

1105
01:13:29.246 --> 01:13:31.919
- No...
- Get the fuck out of here. You're fired!

1106
01:13:32.006 --> 01:13:36.238
I have a better solution. Keep me
on the payroll as an outside consultant.

1107
01:13:36.326 --> 01:13:38.317
In exchange for my salary.

1108
01:13:38.406 --> 01:13:42.081
my job will be never to tell people
these things that I know.

1109
01:13:42.166 --> 01:13:46.284
I don't even have to come into the office.
I can do this job from home.

1110
01:13:47.526 --> 01:13:51.485
Who... Who the fuck do you think you are.
you crazy little shit?

1111
01:13:56.526 --> 01:13:59.916
- Security!
I am Jack's smirking revenge.

1112
01:14:08.526 --> 01:14:10.562
What the hell are you doing?

1113
01:14:19.366 --> 01:14:21.357
That hurt.

1114
01:14:22.766 --> 01:14:24.757
Why would you do that?

1115
01:14:25.366 --> 01:14:28.244
Oh. my God! No! Please stop!

1116
01:14:37.246 --> 01:14:39.237
What are you doing?

1117
01:14:40.286 --> 01:14:42.277
Oh. God. no! Please! No!

1118
01:14:42.366 --> 01:14:46.279
For some reason.
I thought of my first fight. with Tyler.

1119
01:14:46.366 --> 01:14:47.924
No!

1120
01:15:11.326 --> 01:15:15.638
Under and behind and inside
everything this man took for granted.

1121
01:15:15.726 --> 01:15:19.036
something horrible had been growing.

1122
01:15:19.126 --> 01:15:20.161
Look.

1123
01:15:20.246 --> 01:15:24.762
Give me the paychecks. like I asked.
and you won't ever see me again.

1124
01:15:24.846 --> 01:15:27.519
Then. at ourmost excellent
moment together...

1125
01:15:30.446 --> 01:15:33.119
Thank God!
Please don't hit me again.

1126
01:15:33.206 --> 01:15:35.197
Telephone. computer.

1127
01:15:35.286 --> 01:15:40.235
fax machine. 52 weekly paychecks
and 48 airline flight coupons.

1128
01:15:40.326 --> 01:15:42.635
We now had corporate sponsorship.

1129
01:15:42.726 --> 01:15:47.641
This is how Tylerand I were able to have
Fight Club everynight of the week.

1130
01:15:50.206 --> 01:15:53.642
Now. the centre of Fight Club
became the two men fighting.

1131
01:15:53.726 --> 01:15:57.082
The leader walked through the crowd.
out in the darkness.

1132
01:15:58.766 --> 01:16:03.078
Tyler was now involved in
a lawsuit with the Pressman Hotel

1133
01:16:03.166 --> 01:16:05.361
over the urine content of their soup.

1134
01:16:10.326 --> 01:16:13.204
I am Jack's wasted life.

1135
01:16:20.606 --> 01:16:22.597
Thank you. sir.

1136
01:16:24.046 --> 01:16:26.924
Tyler dreamed up
new homework assignments.

1137
01:16:27.006 --> 01:16:29.440
He handed them out in sealed envelopes.

1138
01:17:07.006 --> 01:17:10.521
- There's a Fight Club up in Delaware City.
- Yeah. I heard.

1139
01:17:12.246 --> 01:17:14.362
There's one in Penns Grove too.

1140
01:17:14.446 --> 01:17:16.596
Bob even found one up in New Castle.

1141
01:17:16.686 --> 01:17:19.644
- Did you start that one?
- No. I thought you did.

1142
01:17:19.726 --> 01:17:22.115
No.

1143
01:18:08.846 --> 01:18:08.886
- Stop for a second.
- Hey. what are we doing?

1144
01:18:08.886 --> 01:18:11.081
- Stop for a second.
- Hey. what are we doing?

1145
01:18:11.166 --> 01:18:13.122
- Turn around.
- What are we doing?

1146
01:18:13.206 --> 01:18:15.515
- Homework assignment.
- What kind?

1147
01:18:15.606 --> 01:18:17.562
Human sacrifice.

1148
01:18:17.646 --> 01:18:20.843
- Is that a gun? Please tell me it's not.
- It's a gun.

1149
01:18:20.926 --> 01:18:23.156
- What are you doing?
- Meet me in the back.

1150
01:18:23.246 --> 01:18:25.521
- Don't fuck around!
- Meet me in the back.

1151
01:18:25.606 --> 01:18:27.324
On a long enough time line.

1152
01:18:27.406 --> 01:18:30.159
the survival rate for everyone drops to zero.

1153
01:18:31.126 --> 01:18:33.117
What are you doing? Come on!

1154
01:18:33.206 --> 01:18:36.482
Hands behind your back.
Give me your wallet.

1155
01:18:38.166 --> 01:18:41.317
Raymond K Hessel.
1320 SE Banning. Apartment A.

1156
01:18:42.086 --> 01:18:45.158
- Small. cramped basement apartment?
- How did you know?

1157
01:18:45.246 --> 01:18:47.760
They give shitty apartments letters.

1158
01:18:47.846 --> 01:18:50.838
Raymond! You're going to die.

1159
01:18:50.926 --> 01:18:52.325
No!

1160
01:18:52.406 --> 01:18:56.399
Is that your mom and dad?
They're gonna have to call the kindly doctor.

1161
01:18:56.486 --> 01:18:58.636
Pick up your dental records. Know why?

1162
01:18:58.726 --> 01:19:02.162
- There'll be nothing left of your face.
- Oh. come on!

1163
01:19:02.246 --> 01:19:06.000
An expired community college student ID.
What did you study. Raymond?

1164
01:19:06.086 --> 01:19:08.998
- S... S... Stuff.
- Stuff?

1165
01:19:09.086 --> 01:19:11.077
Were the midterms hard?

1166
01:19:12.166 --> 01:19:14.634
- I asked you what you studied!
- Biology. mostly.

1167
01:19:14.726 --> 01:19:18.082
- Why?
- I don't know.

1168
01:19:18.166 --> 01:19:21.044
What did you wanna be. Raymond K Hessel?!

1169
01:19:22.406 --> 01:19:26.194
The question. Raymond.
was what did you want to be?

1170
01:19:27.806 --> 01:19:29.797
Answer him. Raymond. Jesus!

1171
01:19:29.886 --> 01:19:32.195
- Veterinarian. Veterinarian.
- Animals.

1172
01:19:32.286 --> 01:19:35.119
- Yeah. Animals and stuff.
- Stuff. Yeah. I got that.

1173
01:19:35.206 --> 01:19:37.674
- So you need more schooling.
- Too much school.

1174
01:19:37.766 --> 01:19:40.121
- Would you rather be dead?
- No. please...

1175
01:19:40.206 --> 01:19:44.484
You'd rather die here. on your knees.
in the back of a convenience store?

1176
01:19:44.566 --> 01:19:46.124
Please. no.

1177
01:19:50.046 --> 01:19:52.037
I'm keeping your licence.

1178
01:19:53.246 --> 01:19:56.124
Gonna check in on you.
I know where you live.

1179
01:19:56.206 --> 01:19:59.084
If you're not working
to be a veterinarian in six weeks.

1180
01:19:59.166 --> 01:20:01.157
you will be dead.

1181
01:20:02.966 --> 01:20:04.957
Now run on home.

1182
01:20:09.526 --> 01:20:11.517
Run. Forrest. run!

1183
01:20:13.086 --> 01:20:15.077
I feel ill.

1184
01:20:15.846 --> 01:20:17.837
Imagine how he feels.

1185
01:20:17.926 --> 01:20:19.917
Come on. this isn't funny!

1186
01:20:20.006 --> 01:20:22.315
What the fuck was the point ofthat?!

1187
01:20:22.406 --> 01:20:26.365
Tomorrow will be the most beautiful day
of Raymond K Hessel's life.

1188
01:20:26.446 --> 01:20:30.644
His breakfast will taste better
than any meal you and I have ever tasted.

1189
01:20:32.006 --> 01:20:33.997
You had to give it to him.

1190
01:20:34.086 --> 01:20:36.361
- Come on.
- He had a plan.

1191
01:20:36.446 --> 01:20:39.722
And it started to make sense
in a Tyler-sort of way.

1192
01:20:39.806 --> 01:20:41.637
No fear. No distractions.

1193
01:20:41.726 --> 01:20:44.923
The ability to let that which does not matter

1194
01:20:45.006 --> 01:20:46.917
truly slide.

1195
01:20:59.766 --> 01:21:01.802
You are not your job.

1196
01:21:03.646 --> 01:21:06.877
You're not how much money
you have in the bank.

1197
01:21:08.526 --> 01:21:10.517
You're not the car you drive.

1198
01:21:11.046 --> 01:21:13.765
You're not the contents ofyour wallet.

1199
01:21:13.846 --> 01:21:16.041
You're not your fucking khakis.

1200
01:21:18.766 --> 01:21:22.315
You are the all-singing.
all-dancing crap ofthe world.

1201
01:21:30.806 --> 01:21:32.922
I'll be out of your way in a sec.

1202
01:21:33.686 --> 01:21:35.677
You don't have to go.

1203
01:21:37.126 --> 01:21:39.117
Whatever.

1204
01:21:40.206 --> 01:21:43.164
No. I mean... It's OK.

1205
01:21:52.326 --> 01:21:54.317
Are you still going to groups?

1206
01:21:55.006 --> 01:21:56.997
Yeah.

1207
01:21:58.406 --> 01:22:00.397
Chloe's dead.

1208
01:22:00.886 --> 01:22:02.797
Wow. Chloe.

1209
01:22:02.886 --> 01:22:04.717
When did that happen?

1210
01:22:05.246 --> 01:22:07.043
Do you care?

1211
01:22:07.126 --> 01:22:10.357
I dunno. I haven't thought about it in a while.

1212
01:22:10.606 --> 01:22:12.597
Yeah. well...

1213
01:22:12.686 --> 01:22:14.961
It was the smart move on her part.

1214
01:22:16.286 --> 01:22:18.242
Listen...

1215
01:22:19.446 --> 01:22:21.721
What are you getting out of all this?

1216
01:22:22.406 --> 01:22:24.397
What?

1217
01:22:24.526 --> 01:22:26.756
I mean. all this. Why do you keep...

1218
01:22:27.486 --> 01:22:29.477
Is this making you happy?

1219
01:22:31.006 --> 01:22:32.997
Yeah. well. sometimes.

1220
01:22:34.646 --> 01:22:36.682
I don't know. I don't understand.

1221
01:22:36.766 --> 01:22:40.202
Why does a weaker person
need to latch on to a strong person?

1222
01:22:40.286 --> 01:22:42.277
What is... What is that?

1223
01:22:42.366 --> 01:22:44.436
What do you get out of it?

1224
01:22:45.886 --> 01:22:47.877
No... That's not the same thing at all.

1225
01:22:47.966 --> 01:22:49.957
It's totally different with us.

1226
01:22:50.046 --> 01:22:52.037
Us?

1227
01:22:52.126 --> 01:22:53.957
What do you mean by us?

1228
01:22:54.046 --> 01:22:57.755
- I'm sorry. Do you hear this?
- Hear what?

1229
01:22:57.846 --> 01:22:59.802
- All that noise. Hold on.
- No. wait!

1230
01:22:59.886 --> 01:23:02.480
Don't change the subject!
I want to talk about this.

1231
01:23:02.566 --> 01:23:05.239
- You're not talking about me. are you?
- No.

1232
01:23:05.326 --> 01:23:08.636
- What?
- Playing doctor. What was going on there?

1233
01:23:08.726 --> 01:23:11.843
- What are you talking about?
- Nothing. Nothing.

1234
01:23:11.926 --> 01:23:13.917
- I don't think so.
- What do you want?

1235
01:23:14.006 --> 01:23:16.315
- Look at me.
- No. What?

1236
01:23:17.046 --> 01:23:19.765
- What is that?!
- It's nothing. Don't worry.

1237
01:23:19.846 --> 01:23:22.155
My God. Who did this?

1238
01:23:22.246 --> 01:23:24.237
- A person.
- Guy or girl?

1239
01:23:24.326 --> 01:23:26.999
- What do you care?
- What do you care if I ask?

1240
01:23:27.086 --> 01:23:29.554
- Leave me alone.
- You're afraid to say.

1241
01:23:29.646 --> 01:23:31.557
- I am not. Let me go.
- No! Talk to me.

1242
01:23:31.646 --> 01:23:32.761
