- We're aborting this mission now.
- You said you would definitely say that.

1728
01:57:41.286 --> 01:57:44.676
Are you fucking out of your minds?
You're police officers!

1729
01:57:45.486 --> 01:57:47.477
Is somebody timing this?

1730
01:57:47.646 --> 01:57:50.479
Keep your mouth shut.

1731
01:57:50.566 --> 01:57:52.557
Shit!

1732
01:57:55.086 --> 01:57:57.759
Some of this information checks out.

1733
01:57:57.846 --> 01:58:00.997
- Let's go to that house on Paper Street.
- Be right there.

1734
01:58:01.686 --> 01:58:03.404
Hey. wait!

1735
01:58:04.046 --> 01:58:06.480
- I got him.
- Sir. we have to do this.

1736
01:58:06.566 --> 01:58:08.955
- Stop fighting!
- Where's the rubber band?

1737
01:58:09.046 --> 01:58:11.435
Get away from me! Drop that fucking knife!

1738
01:58:14.846 --> 01:58:18.122
Back up. Face down on the floor right now!

1739
01:58:19.326 --> 01:58:21.282
Get down on the floor!

1740
01:58:25.846 --> 01:58:28.599
The first person
that comes out of this door

1741
01:58:28.686 --> 01:58:30.563
gets a lead salad! Understand?

1742
01:58:53.926 --> 01:58:56.394
Get away! Stay away!

1743
01:59:08.806 --> 01:59:10.797
I ran.

1744
01:59:11.326 --> 01:59:15.319
I ran until my muscles burned
and my veins pumped battery acid.

1745
01:59:17.846 --> 01:59:19.837
Then I ran some more.

1746
01:59:58.846 --> 02:00:01.076
What the fuck are you doing?

1747
02:00:01.166 --> 02:00:03.999
Running around in your underpants!
You look crazy!

1748
02:00:04.086 --> 02:00:07.078
No. I'm onto you.
I know what's going on here.

1749
02:00:07.166 --> 02:00:11.876
Come on. then. I got us a great place
to watch from. It'll be like pay-per-view.

1750
02:00:57.886 --> 02:01:00.446
- Oh. Christ.
- Now what are you doing?

1751
02:01:00.526 --> 02:01:03.757
- I'm stopping this.
- Why?

1752
02:01:03.846 --> 02:01:07.077
- The greatest thing you've ever done.
- I can't let this happen.

1753
02:01:07.166 --> 02:01:10.283
There are 10 other bombs
in 10 other buildings.

1754
02:01:10.366 --> 02:01:12.596
Since when is Project Mayhem
about murder?

1755
02:01:12.686 --> 02:01:14.597
The buildings are empty.

1756
02:01:14.686 --> 02:01:17.405
We're not killing anyone.
We're setting 'em free!

1757
02:01:17.486 --> 02:01:20.159
Bob is dead. They shot him in the head.

1758
02:01:20.246 --> 02:01:23.477
You wanna make an omelette.
you gotta break some eggs.

1759
02:01:23.566 --> 02:01:27.002
No. I'm not listening to you.
You're not even there.

1760
02:01:32.806 --> 02:01:37.004
I wouldn't do that.
Not unless you knew which wires were what.

1761
02:01:37.086 --> 02:01:38.724
If you know. I know.

1762
02:01:44.126 --> 02:01:48.278
Or maybe I knew you'd know. so I spent
all day thinking about the wrong ones.

1763
02:01:56.486 --> 02:01:57.521
You think?

1764
02:01:59.446 --> 02:02:01.437
Oh. heavens. no. Not the green one.

1765
02:02:02.286 --> 02:02:05.164
Pull any one but the green one.

1766
02:02:09.686 --> 02:02:12.200
I asked you not to do that!

1767
02:02:13.966 --> 02:02:15.479
Fuck!

1768
02:02:16.366 --> 02:02:18.402
Tyler. get away from the van.

1769
02:02:20.526 --> 02:02:23.757
Tyler. I'm not kidding!
Get away from the van!

1770
02:02:23.846 --> 02:02:25.165
Goddamn it!

1771
02:02:31.246 --> 02:02:32.565
OK.

1772
02:02:32.646 --> 02:02:35.877
You are now firing a gun
at your imaginary friend

1773
02:02:35.966 --> 02:02:38.434
near 400 gallons of nitroglycerin!

1774
02:02:40.566 --> 02:02:42.238
Cool it. Tyler!

1775
02:02:54.926 --> 02:02:56.917
Come on!

1776
02:02:57.006 --> 02:02:58.962
Don't go!

1777
02:03:35.006 --> 02:03:36.155
What?!

1778
02:04:19.246 --> 02:04:19.406
Three minutes.

1779
02:04:19.406 --> 02:04:21.237
Three minutes.

1780
02:04:21.326 --> 02:04:23.521
This is it.

1781
02:04:23.606 --> 02:04:25.562
The beginning.

1782
02:04:25.646 --> 02:04:27.523
Ground zero.

1783
02:04:27.606 --> 02:04:29.801
I think this is about where we came in.

1784
02:04:29.886 --> 02:04:32.241
Do you have a speech for the occasion?

1785
02:04:32.326 --> 02:04:35.238
I'm sorry?

1786
02:04:35.326 --> 02:04:37.317
I still can't think of anything.

1787
02:04:39.286 --> 02:04:41.277
Flashback humour.

1788
02:04:46.166 --> 02:04:48.122
It's getting exciting now.

1789
02:04:49.606 --> 02:04:51.324
Two and a half.

1790
02:04:51.406 --> 02:04:53.874
Think of everything we've accomplished.

1791
02:04:53.966 --> 02:04:58.562
Out these windows. we will view
the collapse of financial history.

1792
02:04:58.646 --> 02:05:02.195
One step closer to economic equilibrium.

1793
02:05:15.246 --> 02:05:17.521
Why is she here?

1794
02:05:17.606 --> 02:05:19.437
Tying up loose ends.

1795
02:05:19.526 --> 02:05:22.484
Put me down. you bald headed fuck!

1796
02:05:22.566 --> 02:05:25.558
- I beg you. please don't do this.
- I'm not doing this.

1797
02:05:25.646 --> 02:05:28.956
- We are doing this. This is what we want.
- No.

1798
02:05:29.046 --> 02:05:33.562
- I don't want this.
- Right. Except you is meaningless now.

1799
02:05:33.646 --> 02:05:37.480
- We have to forget about you.
- You're a voice in my head.

1800
02:05:37.566 --> 02:05:39.557
You're a voice in mine!

1801
02:05:39.646 --> 02:05:42.365
- Why can't I get rid of you?
- You need me.

1802
02:05:42.446 --> 02:05:44.437
No. I don't. I really don't any more.

1803
02:05:44.526 --> 02:05:48.644
You created me. I didn't create some
loser alter ego to make me feel better.

1804
02:05:48.726 --> 02:05:52.514
- Take some responsibility.
- I do. I am responsible for all of it

1805
02:05:52.646 --> 02:05:54.284
and I accept that.

1806
02:05:54.366 --> 02:05:58.245
So. please. I'm begging you.
please call this off.

1807
02:06:00.166 --> 02:06:02.282
Have I ever let us down?

1808
02:06:03.646 --> 02:06:05.876
How far have you come because of me?!

1809
02:06:11.526 --> 02:06:13.517
I will bring us through this.

1810
02:06:13.606 --> 02:06:17.235
As always. I will carry you
kicking and screaming

1811
02:06:17.326 --> 02:06:19.635
and in the end you will thank me.

1812
02:06:20.126 --> 02:06:22.515
Tyler. Tyler.

1813
02:06:22.606 --> 02:06:25.996
I'm grateful to you.
For everything that you've done for me.

1814
02:06:26.086 --> 02:06:28.646
But this is too much. I don't want this.

1815
02:06:28.726 --> 02:06:33.800
What do you want? Your shit job back?
Fucking condo world. watching sitcoms?

1816
02:06:33.886 --> 02:06:35.877
Fuck you! I won't do it.

1817
02:06:36.686 --> 02:06:40.361
- This can't be happening.
- It's already done. so shut up!

1818
02:06:40.446 --> 02:06:42.004
60 seconds till CRI.

1819
02:06:42.526 --> 02:06:44.517
No.

1820
02:06:46.326 --> 02:06:48.999
I can figure this out. This isn't even real.

1821
02:06:49.086 --> 02:06:52.601
You're not real. that gun...
That gun isn't even in your hand.

1822
02:06:54.046 --> 02:06:56.037
The gun's in my hand.

1823
02:07:00.846 --> 02:07:03.201
Good for you. It doesn't change a thing.

1824
02:07:11.726 --> 02:07:14.286
Why do you wanna put a gun to your head?

1825
02:07:14.366 --> 02:07:16.357
Not my head. Tyler.

1826
02:07:16.926 --> 02:07:18.882
Our head.

1827
02:07:20.326 --> 02:07:22.317
Interesting.

1828
02:07:25.206 --> 02:07:27.766
Where are you going with this. lkea boy?

1829
02:07:33.966 --> 02:07:36.844
Hey. It's you and me.

1830
02:07:39.446 --> 02:07:41.437
Friends?

1831
02:07:42.246 --> 02:07:44.237
Tyler.

1832
02:07:47.526 --> 02:07:49.801
I want you to really listen to me.

1833
02:07:49.886 --> 02:07:52.241
OK.

1834
02:07:52.326 --> 02:07:54.317
My eyes are open.

1835
02:08:12.286 --> 02:08:14.242
What's that smell?

1836
02:08:33.046 --> 02:08:35.924
- Where is everybody?
- Oh. no. What's going on?

1837
02:08:36.566 --> 02:08:38.079
Mr Durden!

1838
02:08:39.126 --> 02:08:40.878
Oh. my God!

1839
02:08:46.046 --> 02:08:49.118
Are you... Are you all right. sir?

1840
02:08:49.206 --> 02:08:52.994
- Oh. yeah. I'm OK.
- You look terrible. sir. What happened?

1841
02:08:53.086 --> 02:08:56.920
- Nothing. it's no problem.
- No. no. no. sir. He's not kidding.

1842
02:08:57.006 --> 02:08:59.645
- You look awful. You need assistance.
- I'm fine.

1843
02:08:59.766 --> 02:09:03.202
Look. I'm fine... Everything's fine.

1844
02:09:05.406 --> 02:09:07.556
Stop it!

1845
02:09:07.646 --> 02:09:10.638
- Let her go.
- Christ Almighty!

1846
02:09:10.726 --> 02:09:12.444
You!

1847
02:09:12.526 --> 02:09:14.517
Hi. Marla.

1848
02:09:15.006 --> 02:09:19.636
- Leave her with me. Meet me downstairs.
- Are you sure?

1849
02:09:19.726 --> 02:09:21.717
Yes. I'm sure.

1850
02:09:22.766 --> 02:09:26.725
You fucker! What kind of sick
fucking game are you playing at?!

1851
02:09:26.806 --> 02:09:29.400
Putting me on a... Oh. my God. your face!

1852
02:09:29.486 --> 02:09:30.919
Yeah. I know.

1853
02:09:35.486 --> 02:09:37.317
What happened?

1854
02:09:37.406 --> 02:09:39.442
- Don't ask.
- You're shot.

1855
02:09:39.526 --> 02:09:41.517
- Yes. I'm shot.
- Oh. my God.

1856
02:09:42.406 --> 02:09:45.318
- I can't believe he's standing.
- One tough motherfucker.

1857
02:09:48.966 --> 02:09:50.763
Who did this?

1858
02:09:50.846 --> 02:09:53.235
I did. actually.

1859
02:09:53.326 --> 02:09:55.317
Find some gauze.

1860
02:09:56.606 --> 02:09:58.562
You shot yourself?

1861
02:09:58.646 --> 02:10:01.206
Yes. but it's OK. Marla. look at me.

1862
02:10:01.286 --> 02:10:03.436
I'm really OK.

1863
02:10:03.526 --> 02:10:07.314
Trust me. Everything's gonna be fine.

1864
02:10:19.606 --> 02:10:23.360
You met me at a very strange time in my life.
